The newly-elected National Chairman of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) Abdullahi Adamu has finally assumed leadership of the party. The Chairman Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) Gov. Mai Mala Buni, formally handed over after about 21 months at the saddle of the party. Also Read: APC Convention: Naysayers Now Disappointed, Says Buhari The brief ceremony took place at the National Working Committee (NWC) Hall at the National Secretariat of the party in Abuja and it was witnessed by all the newly elected executive members and Nasarawa Governor, Abdullahi Sule. The Adamu-led NWC was elected on Saturday at the party’s National Convention in Abuja.